#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:8
msgid "How to Install and Use the Symfony Components"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:10
msgid ""
"If you're starting a new project (or already have a project) that will "
"use one or more components, the easiest way to integrate everything is "
"with `Composer`_. Composer is smart enough to download the component(s) "
"that you need and take care of autoloading so that you can begin using "
"the libraries immediately."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:15
msgid ""
"This article will take you through using :doc:`/components/finder`, "
"though this applies to using any component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:19
msgid "Using the Finder Component"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:21
msgid ""
"**1.** If you're creating a new project, create a new empty directory for"
" it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:23
msgid "**2.** Open a terminal and use Composer to grab the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:29
msgid ""
"The name ``symfony/finder`` is written at the top of the documentation "
"for whatever component you want."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../components/using_components.rst:34
msgid ""
"`Install Composer`_ if you don't have it already present on your system. "
"Depending on how you install, you may end up with a ``composer.phar`` "
"file in your directory. In that case, no worries! Your command line in "
"that case is ``php composer.phar require symfony/finder``."
msgstr ""

